#: ../../topics/projects/index.rst:18
msgid ""
"Salt Sandbox is a multi-VM Vagrant-based Salt development environment used "
"for creating and testing new Salt state modules outside of your production "
"environment. It's also a great way to learn firsthand about Salt and its "
"remote execution capabilities."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/projects/index.rst:23
msgid "Salt Sandbox will set up three separate virtual machines:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/projects/index.rst:25
msgid "salt.example.com - the Salt master server"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/projects/index.rst:26
msgid "minion1.example.com - the first Salt minion machine"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/projects/index.rst:27
msgid "minion2.example.com - the second Salt minion machine"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/projects/index.rst:29
msgid ""
"These VMs can be used in conjunction to segregate and test your modules "
"based on node groups, top file environments, grain values, etc. You can even"
" test modules on different Linux distributions or release versions to better"
" match your production infrastructure."
msgstr ""
